        dbr:Ferdinand_I_of_the_Two_Sicilies,
        dbr:Francis_II%2C_Holy_Roman_Emperor,
        dbr:Friedrich_Wilhelm_von_Buxhoeveden,
        dbr:Gustav_IV_Adolf,
        dbr:Horatio_Nelson%2C_1st_Viscount_Nelson,
        dbr:Jean-de-Dieu_Soult,
        dbr:Joachim_Murat,
        dbr:Karl_Philipp_von_Wrede,
        dbr:Michel_Ney,
        dbr:Mikhail_Kutuzov,
        dbr:Napoleon,
        dbr:Rutger_Jan_Schimmelpenninck,
        dbr:William_Grenville%2C_1st_Baron_Grenville,
        dbr:William_Pitt_the_Younger ;
    sem:hasTimeStamp "1805-04-11"^^xsd:date ;
    sem:subEventOf dbr:French_Revolutionary_and_Napoleonic_Wars ;
    rdfs:comment "The War of the Third Coalition was a European conflict lasting from 1805 to 1806 and was the first conflict of the Napoleonic Wars. During the war, France and its client states under Napoleon I and its ally Spain opposed an alliance, the Third Coalition, which was made up of the United Kingdom, the Austrian Empire, the Russian Empire, Naples, Sicily, and Sweden. Prussia remained neutral during the war." .

dbr:French_invasion_of_Switzerland a sem:Event ;
    sem:hasActor dbr:Alois_von_Reding,
        dbr:Balthazar_Alexis_Henri_Schauenburg,
        dbr:Guillaume_Brune,
        dbr:Karl_Ludwig_von_Erlach ;
    sem:hasPlace dbr:Old_Swiss_Confederacy ;
    sem:hasTimeStamp "1798-05-17"^^xsd:date ;
    sem:subEventOf dbr:French_Revolutionary_Wars ;
    rdfs:comment "The French invasion of Switzerland occurred from January to May 1798 as part of the French Revolutionary Wars. The independent Old Swiss Confederacy collapsed from the invasion and simultaneous internal revolts called the \"Helvetic Revolution\". The Swiss ancien régime institutions were abolished and replaced by the centralised Helvetic Republic, one of the sister republics of the French First Republic." .

dbr:Chouannerie a sem:Event ;
    sem:hasActor dbr:Aim%C3%A9_Picquet_du_Boisguy,
        dbr:Chevalier_de_Boishardy,
        dbr:Claude_Ursule_Gency,
        dbr:Gabriel%2C_comte_d%27H%C3%A9douville,
        dbr:Georges_Cadoudal,
        dbr:Guillaume_Brune,
        dbr:Guillaume_Le_M%C3%A9tayer_dit_Rochambeau,
        dbr:Jean-Louis_Treton,
        dbr:Jean-Michel_Beysser,
        dbr:Jean_Baptiste_Camille_Canclaux,
        dbr:Jean_Chouan,
        dbr:Jean_Joseph_Amable_Humbert,
        dbr:Joseph-Genevi%C3%A8ve_de_Puisaye,
        dbr:Lazare_Hoche,
        dbr:Louis-Marie-Antoine-Auguste-Fortun%C3%A9_d%27Andign%C3%A9,
        dbr:Louis_de_Frott%C3%A9,
        dbr:Marie_Paul_de_Sc%C3%A9peaux_de_Bois-Guignot,
        dbr:Pierre-Mathurin_Mercier_la_Vend%C3%A9e,
        dbr:Pierre_Guillemot,
        dbr:Pierre_Quantin ;
    sem:hasPlace dbr:Normandy ;
    sem:hasTimeStamp "1789-01-01"^^xsd:date ;
    sem:subEventOf dbr:French_Revolutionary_Wars ;
    rdfs:comment "The Chouannerie was a royalist uprising or counter-revolution in twelve of the western départements of France, particularly in the provinces of Brittany and Maine, against the First Republic during the French Revolution. It played out in three phases and lasted from spring 1794 to 1800. The revolt was comparable to the War in the Vendée, which took place in the Vendée region." .

dbr:Quasi-War a sem:Event ;
    sem:hasActor dbr:Andr%C3%A9_Rigaud,
        dbr:Benjamin_Stoddert,
        dbr:Edme_%C3%89tienne_Borne_Desfourneaux,
        dbr:John_Adams,
        dbr:Napoleon,
        dbr:Paul_Barras,
        dbr:Silas_Talbot,
        dbr:Stephen_Decatur,
        dbr:Thomas_Truxtun,
        dbr:Victor_Hugues,
        dbr:William_Bainbridge ;
    sem:hasPlace dbr:Caribbean,
        dbr:East_Coast_of_the_United_States ;
    sem:hasTimeStamp "1798-07-07"^^xsd:date ;
    sem:subEventOf dbr:French_Revolutionary_Wars ;
    rdfs:comment "The Quasi-War was an undeclared war from 1798 to 1800 between the United States and the French First Republic. It was fought almost entirely at sea, primarily in the Caribbean and off the East Coast of the United States, with minor actions in the Indian Ocean and Mediterranean Sea." .

dbr:Italian_campaigns_of_the_French_Revolutionary_Wars a sem:Event ;
    sem:hasActor dbr:Alexander_Suvorov,
        dbr:Am%C3%A9d%C3%A9e_Emmanuel_Fran%C3%A7ois_Laharpe,
        dbr:Andr%C3%A9_Mass%C3%A9na,
        dbr:Charles-Pierre_Augereau,
        dbr:Dagobert_Sigmund_von_Wurmser,
        dbr:Ferdinand_III%2C_Grand_Duke_of_Tuscany,
        dbr:Ferdinand_I_of_the_Two_Sicilies,
        dbr:Fran%C3%A7ois_Christophe_de_Kellermann,
        dbr:Francis_II%2C_Holy_Roman_Emperor,
        dbr:J%C3%B3zsef_Alvinczi,
        dbr:Jean-Mathieu-Philibert_S%C3%A9rurier,
        dbr:Jean_Victor_Marie_Moreau,
        dbr:Louis-Alexandre_Berthier,
        dbr:Louis-Gabriel_Suchet,
        dbr:Michelangelo_Alessandro_Colli-Marchi,
        dbr:Napoleon,
        dbr:Paul_I_of_Russia,
        dbr:Thomas-Alexandre_Dumas ;
    sem:hasPlace dbr:Central_Italy,
        dbr:Northern_Italy ;
    sem:hasTimeStamp "1801-02-09"^^xsd:date ;
    sem:subEventOf dbr:French_Revolutionary_Wars ;
    rdfs:comment "The Italian campaigns of the French Revolutionary Wars (1792–1801) were a series of conflicts fought principally in Northern Italy between the French Revolutionary Army and a Coalition of Austria, Russia, Piedmont-Sardinia, and a number of other Italian states." .

dbr:French_Revolutionary_and_Napoleonic_Wars a sem:Event ;
    sem:hasPlace dbr:Europe ;
    sem:hasTimeStamp "1789-01-01"^^xsd:date ;
    sem:subEventOf dbr:French_Revolution ;
    rdfs:comment "The French Revolutionary and Napoleonic Wars were a series of conflicts between the French and several European monarchies between 1792 and 1815. They encompass first the French Revolutionary Wars against the newly declared French Republic and from 1803 onwards, the Napoleonic Wars against First Consul and later Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte. They include the Coalition Wars as a subset: seven wars waged by various military alliances of great European powers, known as Coalitions, against Revolutionary France – later the First French Empire – and its allies between 1792 and 1815:War of the First Coalition War of the Second Coalition War of" .

dbr:Irish_Rebellion_of_1798 a sem:Event ;
    sem:hasActor dbr:Bagenal_Harvey,
        dbr:Charles_Cornwallis%2C_1st_Marquess_Cornwallis,
        dbr:Gerard_Lake%2C_1st_Viscount_Lake,
        dbr:Henry_Joy_McCracken,
        dbr:Henry_Munro_%28United_Irishman%29,
        dbr:Jean-Baptiste-Fran%C3%A7ois_Bompart,
        dbr:Jean_Joseph_Amable_Humbert,
        dbr:John_Borlase_Warren,
        dbr:John_Murphy_%28priest%29,
        dbr:Michael_Murphy_%28priest%29,
        dbr:Myles_Byrne,
        dbr:Philip_Roche,
        dbr:Ralph_Abercromby,
        dbr:Sir_George_Nugent%2C_1st_Baronet,
        dbr:Thomas_Cloney,
        dbr:William_Aylmer,
        dbr:Wolfe_Tone ;
    sem:hasTimeStamp "1798-10-12"^^xsd:date ;
    sem:subEventOf dbr:French_Revolutionary_Wars ;
    rdfs:comment "The Irish Rebellion of 1798 was a popular insurrection against the British Crown in what was then the separate, but subordinate, Kingdom of Ireland. The main organising force was the Society of United Irishmen. First formed in Belfast by Presbyterians opposed to the landed Anglican establishment, the Society, despairing of reform, sought to secure a republic through a revolutionary union with the country's Catholic majority. The grievances of a rack-rented tenantry drove recruitment." .

dbr:War_of_the_Second_Coalition a sem:Event ;
    sem:hasActor dbr:Charles_Emmanuel_IV,
        dbr:Charles_IV_of_Spain,
        dbr:Ferdinand_III%2C_Grand_Duke_of_Tuscany,
        dbr:Ferdinand_I_of_the_Two_Sicilies,
        dbr:Ferdinand_von_Hompesch_zu_Bolheim,
        dbr:Francis_II%2C_Holy_Roman_Emperor,
        dbr:George_III,
        dbr:Henry_Addington,
        dbr:John_Adams,
        dbr:John_VI_of_Portugal,
        dbr:Maria_Carolina_of_Austria,
        dbr:Maria_I_of_Portugal,
        dbr:Napoleon,
        dbr:Paul_Barras,
        dbr:Paul_I_of_Russia,
        dbr:Republic_of_Lucca,
        dbr:Selim_III,
        dbr:Tipu_Sultan,
        dbr:William_Pitt_the_Younger ;
    sem:hasPlace dbr:Italian_campaigns_of_the_French_Revolutionary_Wars ;
    sem:hasTimeStamp "1798-06-28"^^xsd:date ;
    sem:subEventOf dbr:French_Revolutionary_Wars,
        dbr:French_Revolutionary_and_Napoleonic_Wars ;
    rdfs:comment "The War of the Second Coalition (1798–1802) was the second war between revolutionary France and a coalition of European monarchies, led by Britain, Austria and Russia, and including the Ottoman Empire, Portugal, Naples and various German monarchies. Prussia did not join the coalition, while Spain supported France." .

dbr:French_Revolutionary_Wars a sem:Event ;
    sem:hasActor dbr:Alexander_Suvorov,
        dbr:Archduke_Charles%2C_Duke_of_Teschen,
        dbr:Charles_Fran%C3%A7ois_Dumouriez,
        dbr:Charles_IV_of_Spain,
        dbr:Charles_William_Ferdinand%2C_Duke_of_Brunswick,
        dbr:Dagobert_Sigmund_von_Wurmser,
        dbr:Fran%C3%A7ois_Christophe_de_Kellermann,
        dbr:Fran%C3%A7ois_S%C3%A9bastien_Charles_Joseph_de_Croix%2C_Count_of_Clerfayt,
        dbr:Fyodor_Ushakov,
        dbr:Henri_de_la_Rochejaquelein,
        dbr:Horatio_Nelson%2C_1st_Viscount_Nelson,
        dbr:Jean-Baptiste_Robert_Lindet,
        dbr:John_VI_of_Portugal,
        dbr:Louis_Joseph%2C_Prince_of_Cond%C3%A9,
        dbr:Louis_Philippe_I,
        dbr:Louis_XVI,
        dbr:Napoleon,
        dbr:Prince_Frederick%2C_Duke_of_York_and_Albany,
        dbr:Ralph_Abercromby,
        dbr:Tipu_Sultan ;
    sem:hasPlace dbr:Middle_East ;
    sem:hasTimeStamp "1789-01-01"^^xsd:date ;
    sem:subEventOf dbr:French_Revolution,
        dbr:French_Revolutionary_and_Napoleonic_Wars ;
    rdfs:comment "The French Revolutionary Wars were a series of sweeping military conflicts resulting from the French Revolution that lasted from 1792 until 1802. They pitted France against Great Britain, Austria, Prussia, Russia, and several other countries. The wars are divided into two periods: the War of the First Coalition (1792–1797) and the War of the Second Coalition (1798–1802). Initially confined to Europe, the fighting gradually assumed a global dimension. After a decade of constant warfare and aggressive diplomacy, France had conquered territories in the Italian peninsula, the Low Countries, and the Rhineland with its very large and powerful military which had" .

dbr:War_of_the_First_Coalition a sem:Event ;
    sem:hasActor dbr:Charles_IV_of_Spain,
        dbr:Charles_William_Ferdinand%2C_Duke_of_Brunswick,
        dbr:Ferdinand_I_of_the_Two_Sicilies,
        dbr:Francis_II%2C_Holy_Roman_Emperor,
        dbr:Frederick_William_II_of_Prussia,
        dbr:George_III,
        dbr:Jacques_Pierre_Brissot,
        dbr:Louis_XVI,
        dbr:Maximilien_Robespierre,
        dbr:Napoleon,
        dbr:Paul_Barras,
        dbr:William_Pitt_the_Younger ;
    sem:hasPlace dbr:Low_Countries ;
    sem:hasTimeStamp "1792-04-20"^^xsd:date ;
    sem:subEventOf dbr:French_Revolutionary_Wars,
        dbr:French_Revolutionary_and_Napoleonic_Wars ;
    rdfs:comment "The War of the First Coalition was a set of wars between a coalition of several European powers and France fought between 1792 and 1797. The coalition was only loosely allied and fought without much coordination; each power wanted to annex a different part of France should they defeat the French, something that never occurred." .

